In [4]:
landsat_dname = os.path.join(base_dname, 'Landsat', 'SceneSubset')
scene_fnames = [f for f in os.listdir(landsat_dname) if not 'cloud' in f]
scene_data = {}

scene_dates = []
for scene in scene_fnames:
    year = scene[9:13]
    jday = scene[13:16]
    date = dt.datetime(int(year), 1, 1, 12) + dt.timedelta(int(jday))
    scene_dates.append(date)
    scene_data[date] = rasterio.open(os.path.join(landsat_dname, scene)).read(1)
    
scene_dates.sort()

%matplotlib notebook
import matplotlib as mpl
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid
import numpy as np

fig = plt.figure(1, (12., 12.))
grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,  # similar to subplot(111)
                 nrows_ncols=(5, 4),  # creates 2x2 grid of axes
                 axes_pad=0.2,  # pad between axes in inch.
                 share_all=True,
                    cbar_location="bottom",
                    cbar_mode="single",)

for i, scene_date in enumerate(scene_dates):
    im =grid[i].imshow(scene_data[scene_date], vmin=0., vmax=.5, cmap=mpl.cm.summer_r)
    grid[i].set_title(scene_date.strftime("%Y-%m-%d"), fontsize=10)
    pyphenocam.plotting.format_photo_axes(grid[i])
grid.cbar_axes[0].colorbar(im)
